context: The FBI has maintained files on numerous people, <a0_0>including celebrities such as <b4_0>Elvis Presley<b4_0/><a0_0/>, <b8_0>Frank Sinatra<b8_0/>, John Denver, John Lennon, Jane Fonda, Groucho Marx, Charlie Chaplin, the band MC5, Lou Costello, Sonny Bono, Bob Dylan, Michael Jackson, and Mickey Mantle. The files were collected for various reasons. Some of the subjects were investigated for alleged ties to the <a3_0>Communist party<a3_0/> (<b5_0>Charlie Chaplin<b5_0/> and Groucho Marx), or in connection with <a1_0>antiwar activities<a1_0/> during the Vietnam War (<b6_0>John Denver<b6_0/>, John Lennon, and Jane Fonda). Numerous celebrity files concern <a2_0>threats or extortion attempts<a2_0/> against them (<b7_0>Sonny Bono<b7_0/>, John Denver, John Lennon, Elvis Presley, Michael Jackson, Mickey Mantle, Groucho Marx, and Frank Sinatra).
